==Latin==
===Etymology===
Ablative case of [[sensus]] "sense" and [[latus]] "broad".

===Adverb===
'''sensu lato'''
# In the broad sense.

===Antonyms===
* [[sensu stricto]]

==Translingual==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} : ''sensu lato'', in the broad sense.

===Adverb===
'''''sensu lato'''''
# {{botany}} In the broad sense.
:''The circumscription of the family ''Malvaceae'' in the APG II system is much more wide than previously accepted. The family in its wider circumscripton can be indicated as ''Malvaceae sensu lato.

===Antonyms===
* [[sensu stricto]]